race.comment: BOLD AND BLAZEN (4) starting to hit his straps this time in and chasing his third-straight victory today. Up in weight today after clearing out from the sticky draw when a dominant winner over 1350m at Wyong. Will get across from the draw and a fitness edge over most of these. SMART SERENADE (8) will relish the claim after he gripped on late for a respectable third over 1300m at Hawkesbury in BM64 grade. Sure to be thereabouts. TENBURY WELLS (2) handy gelding worth thought first up with Grima's 3kg claim. Fitted with the one trial and look for him closing late. ANGARA (3) goes well on his home track on the quick backup. Senior rider goes on and goes into the exotics. VIS I DO (12) caught the eye last start and gets a better set-up for this.
